  "body": "Currently playing around with hardhat + docker and I am running into an issue where it does not seem to fail due to not having the correct permissions to write the config file.\r\n\r\nIf I were building a docker image for this I could just inject the config file, but for right now my goal is to not need to build a new docker image every time I am trying to test it. I am just using docker as a guaranteed running environment.\r\n\r\nThis is the error I am seeing:\r\n```\r\nCreating uniswap-exporter_scraper_run ... done\r\n/app # npx hardhat\r\nAn unexpected error occurred:\r\n\r\nError: EACCES: permission denied, mkdir '/root/.config/hardhat-nodejs'\r\n    at Object.mkdirSync (node:fs:1014:3)\r\n    at Object.mkdirsSync (/app/node_modules/hardhat/node_modules/fs-extra/lib/mkdirs/mkdirs-sync.js:31:9)\r\n    at getConfigDirSync (/app/node_modules/hardhat/src/internal/util/global-dir.ts:27:6)\r\n    at Object.hasConsentedTelemetry (/app/node_modules/hardhat/src/internal/util/global-dir.ts:109:21)\r\n    at main (/app/node_modules/hardhat/src/internal/cli/cli.ts:120:49) {\r\n  errno: -13,\r\n  syscall: 'mkdir',\r\n  code: 'EACCES',\r\n  path: '/root/.config/hardhat-nodejs'\r\n}\r\nnpm notice \r\nnpm notice New minor version of npm available! 7.5.3 -> 7.6.0\r\nnpm notice Changelog: https://github.com/npm/cli/releases/tag/v7.6.0\r\nnpm notice Run npm install -g npm@7.6.0 to update!\r\nnpm notice \r\nnpm ERR! code 1\r\nnpm ERR! path /app\r\nnpm ERR! command failed\r\nnpm ERR! command sh -c hardhat\r\n\r\nnpm ERR! A complete log of this run can be found in:\r\nnpm ERR!     /root/.npm/_logs/2021-02-27T05_33_11_991Z-debug.log\r\n```",
