    "body": "@fvictorio \r\nOkay, just had reason to dust off the ol' project, definitely still an issue and I can confirm your test does not encounter it.\r\n\r\nTo reproduce, run\r\n\r\n```sh\r\ngit clone git@github.com:nomiclabs/hardhat-hackathon-boilerplate.git\r\ncd hardhat-hackathon-boilerplate\r\n# do this outside of docker to simulate my situation of not wanting to build a custom image\r\nnpm i\r\ndocker run -it --rm -v \"$(pwd)\":/app -w /app --entrypoint npm node:16-alpine run test\r\n```\r\n\r\nAnd then I get the same error as before. The only fix I have yet found is to mount `~:/root` which is very non-ideal.\r\n\r\nI like being able to use docker for testing sometimes so I know it is the same node and npm config across platforms and when developing I often don't want to make a new docker image after every change. And of course I set it up with my IDE so it is just a quick one-line call.",
